%% OSPP Full Offline BLE Session Flow
%% Reference: spec/04-flows.md, Section 5a; examples/flows/04-full-offline-session.md
%% Scenario: Both phone and station are offline (no MQTT, no internet)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor User as 📱 Mobile App
    participant BLE as 📶 BLE Radio
    participant Station as ⚙️ Station Controller

    Note over User,Station: Prerequisites: User has valid OfflinePass (pre-armed), station has no MQTT

    %% BLE Discovery
    rect rgb(243, 229, 245)
        Note over User,Station: Phase 1 — BLE Discovery & Connection
        User->>User: Scan for BLE advertisements
        BLE-->>User: Advertisement (stationId, stationName)
        User->>BLE: GATT Connect
        BLE-->>User: Connected (MTU negotiated)
        User->>BLE: Read FFF1 (Station Info)
        BLE-->>User: {stationId, firmwareVersion, capabilities}
        User->>BLE: Read FFF2 (Available Services)
        BLE-->>User: {bays: [{bayId, status, services}]}
    end

    %% Handshake
    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over User,Station: Phase 2 — ECDH Handshake
        User->>BLE: Write FFF3: Hello {deviceId, appNonce}
        BLE-->>User: Notify FFF4: Challenge {stationNonce, stationConnectivity: "Offline"}
        Note over User: Detects full offline scenario
        User->>User: Derive session key (HKDF-SHA256)
    end

    %% OfflinePass Authorization
    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over User,Station: Phase 3 — OfflinePass Authorization
        User->>BLE: Write FFF3: OfflineAuthRequest
        Note right of User: {offlinePass, counter, sessionProof}
        Station->>Station: Validate OfflinePass (10 checks)
        Note over Station: 1.Signature 2.Expiry 3.Epoch<br/>4.Device 5.Station 6.MaxUses<br/>7.MaxCredits 8.PerTx 9.Rate 10.Counter
        BLE-->>User: Notify FFF4: AuthResponse {result: "Accepted"}
    end

    %% Service Start
    rect rgb(225, 245, 254)
        Note over User,Station: Phase 4 — Service Delivery
        User->>BLE: Write FFF3: StartServiceRequest {bayId, serviceId, durationSeconds}
        Station->>Station: Activate hardware
        BLE-->>User: Notify FFF4: StartServiceResponse {result: "Accepted"}
    end

    %% Metering via BLE notifications
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Station,User: Every 5 seconds — BLE notifications
        loop Service Status Updates
            BLE-->>User: Notify FFF5: {status: "Running", meterValues, elapsedSec, remainingSec}
            User->>User: Update UI with real-time consumption
        end
    end

    %% Service Stop
    User->>BLE: Write FFF3: StopServiceRequest {bayId, sessionId}
    Station->>Station: Deactivate hardware, generate receipt
    BLE-->>User: Notify FFF4: StopServiceResponse {result: "Accepted", meterValues}

    %% Receipt
    rect rgb(252, 228, 236)
        Note over User,Station: Phase 5 — Receipt & Disconnect
        BLE-->>User: Notify FFF5: {status: "ReceiptReady"}
        User->>BLE: Read FFF6 (Receipt)
        BLE-->>User: {receipt: {data, signature, signatureAlgorithm: "ECDSA-P256-SHA256"}}
        User->>User: Store receipt + offline tx locally
        User->>BLE: Disconnect
    end

    Note over User,Station: Transaction stored locally on both sides
    Note over Station: When MQTT reconnects → TransactionEvent sent to server
    Note over User: When internet returns → App syncs offline tx with server
